Subject: MDKSA-2003:067 - Updated ethereal packages fix multiple vulnerabilities


-----BEGIN PGP SIGNED MESSAGE-----
Hash: SHA1

________________________________________________________________________

                Mandrake Linux Security Update Advisory
________________________________________________________________________

Package name:           ethereal
Advisory ID:            MDKSA-2003:067
Date:                   June 16th, 2003

Affected versions:	9.1
________________________________________________________________________

Problem Description:

 Several vulnerabilities in ethereal were discovered by Timo Sirainen.
 Integer overflows were found in the Mount and PPP dissectors, as well
 as one-byte buffer overflows in the AIM, GIOP Gryphon, OSPF, PPTP,
 Quake, Quake2, Quake3, Rsync, SMB, SMPP, and TSP dissectors.  These
 vulnerabilties were corrected in ethereal 0.9.12.
________________________________________________________________________

References:
  
  http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CAN-2003-0356
  http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CAN-2003-0357
  http://www.ethereal.com/appnotes/enpa-sa-00009.html
________________________________________________________________________

Updated Packages:
  
 Mandrake Linux 9.1:
